I hardly leave my house anymore so yeah MY life kind of is. Overall, there are a lot more people living on the streets than in the past and hard drugs are everywhere, but I don't see much direct exposure to them. It's sad because things could be/used to be so good here, really they still are pretty good when you look at certain communities in isolation. Honestly our city government is a joke, it's almost all business owners and developers jockeying for their own interests and that along with covid/lack of federal support for businesses has done a lot of damage. As far as the people go, I think most you'd meet around are just fine, it's a wide mix and not %90 queer leftists like you might expect. That community is still really strong here and for the most part I'd say they are just being themselves and supporting eachother and that's nice I think. Same thing with other sorts of people, there are a lot of blue collar and tech folks here too. Most people are pretty accepting of eachother. In my experience it's usually the rich old fucks who are assholes. Almost all of the people I have met have been nice, though I know there has to be evil out there too. It feels like there is so much amazing stuff happening all around all the time, people making art and coming together, but my life is really pretty insular I only have a couple friends and don't go out a lot, and even when I do it often feels like there's a lot of distance between people and I don't know how to cross it.
